This file preserves previous versions of the skill before amendments.

## v1.2.0 (2026-06-19)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus — 2026-06-19 mypy 2.1.0 broken-main session.

**Verification:** verified-ci (the fix-main PR #1530 merged green through the
required-checks gate; `pixi run mypy` then reported `Success: no issues found in
N source files`; all 4 dependent PRs merged green).

**What changed:** Added a THIRD tool variant of the same `pass_filenames: false`
whole-tree-hook root cause: `pixi run mypy`. The `mypy-check-python` pre-commit
hook (`entry: pixi run mypy`, `pass_filenames: false`,
`files: ^(hephaestus|scripts|tests)/.*\.py$`) type-checks the ENTIRE tree on
every commit, so a mypy 2.1.0 version bump that newly flagged pre-existing test
code aborted every commit/PR (including unrelated ones) and made main's required
`lint`/Required Checks RED — CI's `lint` job runs the SAME hook, so local == CI.
Extended the `description` (mypy type-error variant + version-bump trigger),
added a mypy bullet to "When to Use" (with the two concrete 2.1.0 errors), added
three Failed Attempts rows (blanket / `[attr-defined]` ignore vs the correct
`[method-assign]` under `warn_unused_ignores=true`; passing a file arg to
`pixi run mypy` → "Duplicate module" error; trusting a `lint` "pass" that was
actually SKIPPED by the `changes-gate` on an auto-merge event), extended
Results & Parameters with the type-check variant, the changes-gate skipped-lint
caveat, PR/issue refs (#1530, issue #1529; dependents #1531/#1533/#1535/#1537),
and the expected `Success: no issues found in N source files` output. Reinforced
the "fix broken main FIRST in a one-file prereq PR, then stack" pattern as
applying to mypy. Bumped Overview to "three variants" and date to 2026-06-19.

**Why:** A sibling root cause surfaced under the SAME diagnostic signature
("pre-commit fails on a file I never touched; empty `git diff` vs origin/main;
main's required `lint` is already RED"). This time the blocker was a tree-wide
mypy TYPE error after a mypy 2.1.0 bump, not `ruff format` drift or a
`ruff check` lint. Two real fixes: (1) change a `mock.MagicMock()` method
assignment's ignore from `[attr-defined]` to the EXACT `[method-assign]` code
mypy 2.1.0 now emits (a blanket ignore double-errors under
`warn_unused_ignores=true`); (2) import `AGENT_COMMIT_MESSAGE` /
`AGENT_PR_MESSAGE` from their canonical module `session_naming` instead of via
`pr_manager`, which only imports (not re-exports) them and is rejected under
`implicit_reexport=false`. Two new secondary gotchas: do NOT pass a file arg to
the bare `pixi run mypy` task (→ "Duplicate module" error), and a `lint` check
can show "pass" while actually SKIPPED by the `changes-gate` on an auto-merge
event (a skip counts as PASS at the required-checks-gate). The fix shape matched
the original skill: land prereq PR #1530 (issue #1529) merged FIRST to re-green
main, then stack the dependents #1531/#1533/#1535/#1537 on it; all merged green.

